{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (0 blocking, 8 advisory). Triage — all 8 valid, remediation plan:\n1. [T3] setup-project.sh only RESOLVES group UUIDs, doesn't CREATE — will add idempotent create-group (SSH create-group / REST PUT /a/groups) before the ls-groups resolution.\n2. [E5] Add a LIVE submit test: push a test change and submit it via merge-if-necessary to prove the pinned strategy actually merges (not just that config parsed).\n3. [E1] 'three ACLs' = three permission TYPES (Create Reference, Delete Reference, Push Merge Commit); Push Merge Commit is applied to two ref-patterns (refs/for/refs/heads/main + refs/for/refs/heads/feature/*). Will state this explicitly so the count is unambiguous.\n4. [G1G2] Update the stale hardcoded commit message at setup-project.sh:82.\n5. [T5b] ACL enforcement is Gerrit-NATIVE (server rejects the push/ref-op and records it in Gerrit's sshd/httpd audit log) — the bot is not in that path, so a rebar metric is not warranted; will document 'signals to watch' (Gerrit audit log) in the runbook (S4) instead. Justified light-touch.\n6. [T1] Pre-flight/post-flight: after pushing config, read the label back via REST and ASSERT copyCondition contains MERGE_FIRST_PARENT_UPDATE (Gerrit drops/normalizes unknown predicates) — catches a version-gated/mis-spelled token immediately, not at S5.\n7. [E6/F1] Quiet-window proof: query /a/changes/?q=status:open+project:rebar+branch:main and confirm empty BEFORE applying the [submit] pin.\n8. [T9] Document the group RETIRE path (revoke ACLs + delete/empty the group) in the amending ADR back-out section (dovetails with S6 back-out)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783054526711560001,"uuid":"ba06282a-d5c8-4d2d-8069-ee4709417812"}